{
  "text": "Following the description of mouse embryo development by [CITATION_1] , the anatomy ontology is organized into 26 developmental stages, referred to as Theiler stages (TS1-TS26). Each stage is primarily organized as a structural part-of tree. Figure 1 shows part of the top three levels of the tree at TS6. (The browser shown in the figure is available on-line at the Mouse Atlas* web site.)",
  "citation_candidates": [
